## 7. Machine Learning Details

### 7.1 Problem Formulation

**Problem Type:** Supervised Regression

**Objective:** Predict parking occupancy percentage (0-100%) for a given zone at a specific time

**Approach:** Train separate models per zone or a single multi-zone model with zone embeddings

### 7.2 Input Features

#### 7.2.1 Core Features

| Feature Category | Features | Type | Example |
|-----------------|----------|------|---------|
| **Location** | Zone ID | Categorical | "ZONE_001" |
| | Zone Type | Categorical | "Street", "Garage", "Lot" |
| | Zone Capacity | Numerical | 150 |
| | District | Categorical | "Downtown", "Suburbs" |
| | Latitude | Numerical | 23.0225 |
| | Longitude | Numerical | 72.5714 |
| **Time** | Hour of Day | Numerical (0-23) | 14 |
| | Day of Week | Categorical | "Monday" |
| | Is Weekend | Binary | 0/1 |
| | Month | Categorical | "January" |
| | Is Holiday | Binary | 0/1 |
| | Season | Categorical | "Winter", "Summer" |
| **Events** | Event Nearby | Binary | 0/1 |
| | Event Type | Categorical | "Sports", "Concert", "Festival" |
| | Event Distance | Numerical (km) | 0.5 |
| | Event Capacity | Numerical | 10000 |
| **Traffic** | Traffic Density | Numerical (0-1) | 0.75 |
| | Average Speed | Numerical (km/h) | 25 |
| | Road Closure | Binary | 0/1 |
| **Historical** | Avg Occupancy Last Hour | Numerical (%) | 65 |
| | Avg Occupancy Same Hour Yesterday | Numerical (%) | 70 |
| | Avg Occupancy Same Hour Last Week | Numerical (%) | 68 |
| | Rolling 7-day Average | Numerical (%) | 67 |

#### 7.2.2 Engineered Features

- **Temporal Patterns:**
  - Is Rush Hour (7-9 AM, 5-7 PM)
  - Is Lunch Time (12-2 PM)
  - Is Late Night (10 PM - 6 AM)
  
- **Cyclical Encoding:**
  - Hour_sin = sin(2π × hour/24)
  - Hour_cos = cos(2π × hour/24)
  - Day_sin = sin(2π × day/7)
  - Day_cos = cos(2π × day/7)

- **Interaction Features:**
  - Zone_Type × Is_Weekend
  - Hour × Event_Nearby
  - District × Is_Holiday

### 7.3 Target Variable

**Occupancy Percentage:**
- Range: 0-100%
- Definition: (Occupied Spots / Total Capacity) × 100
- **Availability = 100 - Occupancy**

### 7.4 Model Selection

#### 7.4.1 Baseline Model
- **Simple Moving Average:** Average of last 3 same-weekday occupancy values
- **Purpose:** Establish minimum performance threshold

#### 7.4.2 Candidate Models

**1. Linear Regression**
- Fast training and inference
- Interpretable coefficients
- Good for linear relationships
- **Use Case:** Baseline statistical model

**2. Random Forest**
- Handles non-linear relationships
- Robust to outliers
- Feature importance analysis
- No extensive feature scaling needed
- **Use Case:** Strong baseline with interpretability

**3. Gradient Boosting (XGBoost)**
- State-of-the-art performance
- Handles complex interactions
- Built-in regularization
- Efficient training
- **Use Case:** Primary production model

**4. Neural Networks (Future)**
- Deep feature learning
- Captures complex patterns
- Scalable to large datasets
- **Use Case:** When dataset size increases significantly

#### 7.4.3 Model Ensemble
- Weighted average of Random Forest and XGBoost predictions
- Weights determined by validation performance
- **Purpose:** Improve robustness and accuracy

### 7.5 Model Training Pipeline

```
Raw Data
    ↓
Data Validation & Cleaning
    ↓
Feature Engineering
    ↓
Train-Validation-Test Split (70-15-15)
    ↓
Feature Scaling (StandardScaler)
    ↓
Model Training (with Cross-Validation)
    ↓
Hyperparameter Tuning (Grid/Random Search)
    ↓
Model Evaluation
    ↓
Model Selection
    ↓
Final Model Training on Train+Validation
    ↓
Test Set Evaluation
    ↓
Model Serialization & Deployment
```

### 7.6 Training Configuration

**Data Split:**
- Training: 70% (maintains temporal order)
- Validation: 15%
- Test: 15%
- **Note:** No data leakage from future to past

**Cross-Validation:**
- Time-series cross-validation (expanding window)
- 5 folds
- Ensures temporal integrity

**Hyperparameter Tuning:**
- XGBoost parameters:
  - max_depth: [3, 5, 7, 10]
  - learning_rate: [0.01, 0.05, 0.1]
  - n_estimators: [100, 200, 500]
  - subsample: [0.8, 1.0]
  - colsample_bytree: [0.8, 1.0]

- Random Forest parameters:
  - n_estimators: [100, 200, 500]
  - max_depth: [10, 20, None]
  - min_samples_split: [2, 5, 10]
  - min_samples_leaf: [1, 2, 4]

### 7.7 Model Output

**Prediction Object:**
```json
{
  "zone_id": "ZONE_001",
  "prediction_time": "2026-02-07T15:00:00Z",
  "predicted_availability": 45.3,
  "confidence_score": 82.5,
  "prediction_range": {
    "lower_bound": 38.1,
    "upper_bound": 52.5
  },
  "model_version": "v1.2.3",
  "features_used": ["hour", "day", "event_nearby", "historical_avg"]
}
```

**Confidence Score Calculation:**
- Based on prediction interval width
- Historical model accuracy for similar conditions
- Data quality indicators
- Formula: `100 - (prediction_std / mean_prediction × 100)`

### 7.8 Model Evaluation

#### 7.8.1 Regression Metrics

| Metric | Formula | Target |
|--------|---------|--------|
| **MAE** | Mean Absolute Error | < 10% |
| **RMSE** | Root Mean Square Error | < 15% |
| **MAPE** | Mean Absolute Percentage Error | < 12% |
| **R² Score** | Coefficient of Determination | > 0.75 |

#### 7.8.2 Classification Metrics (Availability Levels)
Convert predictions to categories: High (>60%), Medium (30-60%), Low (<30%)

- **Accuracy:** Correct category predictions / Total predictions
- **Precision/Recall:** Per category performance
- **Confusion Matrix:** Category misclassification analysis

#### 7.8.3 Business Metrics
- **User Trust:** Confidence score vs actual accuracy correlation
- **Decision Quality:** Percentage of users finding parking in predicted zones
- **Time Saved:** Reduction in average parking search time

### 7.9 Model Monitoring & Retraining

**Monitoring:**
- Daily prediction accuracy tracking
- Feature drift detection
- Concept drift monitoring (seasonal changes)
- Alert triggers:
  - MAE exceeds 15% for 3 consecutive days
  - Significant feature distribution shift
  - New zones added

**Retraining Schedule:**
- **Regular:** Monthly retraining with latest data
- **Triggered:** When monitoring alerts fire
- **Seasonal:** Before major seasonal changes (festival seasons, weather changes)

**A/B Testing:**
- Deploy new model to 10% of traffic initially
- Compare performance against current model
- Gradual rollout if performance improves

