- Critical bugs discovered
- Performance degradation > 20%
- Error rate > 5%
- Manual decision by on-call engineer

**Process:**
1. Automated health check failure triggers alert
2. On-call engineer investigates
3. Decision to rollback made
4. Previous Docker image redeployed
5. Database migrations rolled back (if applicable)
6. Cache cleared
7. Monitoring confirms rollback success

**Target:** Rollback completion within 15 minutes

### 12.5 Monitoring & Alerting

**Metrics to Monitor:**
- API response time (p50, p95, p99)
- Error rate (4xx, 5xx responses)
- Database query performance
- Model prediction latency
- System resource usage (CPU, memory, disk)
- Active users
- Prediction accuracy drift

**Alerting Conditions:**
- API response time > 5 seconds for 5 minutes
- Error rate > 5% for 5 minutes
- Database connection failures
- Disk usage > 85%
- Model accuracy drops below threshold

**Tools:**
- Prometheus (metrics collection)
- Grafana (visualization)
